[stable]
version=1.6.4
url=https://albar965.github.io/release/2017/09/22/littlenavmap-stable-164-released.html
downloadwin=https://github.com/albar965/littlenavmap/releases/download/v1.6.4/LittleNavmap-win-1.6.4.zip
downloadmac=https://github.com/albar965/littlenavmap/releases/download/v1.6.4/LittleNavmap-macOS-1.6.4.zip
downloadlinux=https://github.com/albar965/littlenavmap/releases/download/v1.6.4/LittleNavmap-linux-1.6.4.tar.gz
changelog=
  <p><b>This update fixes several crashes when loading X-Plane scenery.</b></p>
  <p><b>Changes from Release 1.6.3 to 1.6.4</b></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Fixed crashes when reading X-Plane CIFP files with unknown approach type.</li>
    <li>Fixed crash with older X-Plane `apt.dat` files where runway name for VASI is missing.</li>
    <li>Fixed error where altitude restrictions were not recognized when given as flight levels.</li>
    <li>Enabled support for older `apt.dat` files with version down to 850.</li>
    <li>Added support for all altitude restriction types in procedures.</li>
    <li>Improved error reporting reading X-Plane dat files to avoid crash to desktop.</li>
    <li>Added error collection for X-Plane compiler. Now only stops reading the current file on error.</li>
    <li>Added workaround for P3D v4 add-on.xml files with inconsistent encoding.</li>
    <li>Fixed inconsistencies around context menus and procedure restriction display.</li>
    <li>Moved hidden URL to top in update notification dialog.</li>
    <li>Updated included PDF manual.
  </ul>
  <hr/>
  <small>
  <p><b>Previous Changes from Release 1.4.4 to 1.6.3</b></p>
    <p>Most changes are regarding X-Plane support but installation of this update is also recommended for FSX or Prepar3D users due to several bug fixes and small improvements.</p>
  <p>The scenery database format has changed since 1.4.4 and the program will ask to erase its own databases if started. The <code>Load Scenery Library</code> dialog will open after removing the old databases.</p>
  <p><em>Little Navconnect</em> is now included in the <em>Little Navmap</em> download archive in a sub-directory.</p>
  <p>The <em>Little Xpconnect</em> X-Plane plugin included in the <em>Little Navmap</em> download archive.</p>
  <p><b>Full support for X-Plane 11</b></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Scenery database: Airports, aprons, taxiways, navaids, airways, procedures (SIDs, STARs, ...) and all.</li>
    <li>Read and decode the downloaded X-Plane weather files.</li>
    <li>Copy airspaces from FSX/P3D to X-Plane database.</li>
    <li>Can load and save FMS files.</li>
    <li>Moving map (needs included <em>Little XpConnect</em> plugin) also allowing remote setups.</li>
    <li>Displays AI traffic.</li>
    <li>Flight plan calculation considers additional maximum altitude and one-way restrictions.</li>
    <li>Enabled database file exclusions and add-on override options to X-Plane loader.</li>
    <li>Speed limit for procedure segments.</li>
    <li>All for Windows, macOS and Linux.</li>
  </ul>
  <p><b>General Improvements</b></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Automatic update check with notification and settings in dialog <code>Options</code> on tab <code>Startup</code>.</li>
    <li><em>Active Sky for Prepar3D v4</em> weather now supported.</li>
    <li>Rhumb line measurement now shows both magnetic and true course where declination is based on origin.</li>
    <li>Improved weather display for nearest station: Added name, distance and map link to reporting station if the station is an airport.</li>
    <li>Route string generation is now more robust for malformed and incomplete flight plans.</li>
    <li>Added buttons to clear selection and reset search in search dock window and flight plan window.</li>
    <li>Now erasing wrong airway entries at departure and destination when loading flight plan to avoid problems with malformed files from other tools.</li>
    <li>Can now load FMS, FLP and FS9 ini-style PLN flight plan formats.</li>
    <li>Shows startup positions in the information window now.</li>
    <li>Database loading dialog now pops up after erasing incompatible databases.</li>
    <li>Added donation link to help menu and about dialog.</li>
  </ul>
  <p><b>Bug Fixes</b></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Fixed multiple problems with magnetic declination by using <code>magdec.bgl</code> file.</li>
    <li>Several problems fixed when loading FSX/P3D scenery databases and P3D v4 <code>add-on.xml</code>.</li>
    <li>Corrected handling and display of helipads. Now using name as an identifier.</li>
    <li>Fixed missing encoding in saved PLN files which caused problems with other tools.</li>
    <li>Better detection of military airports name capitalization.</li>
  </ul>
  </small>
  
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
[beta]
version=1.6.1.beta
downloadwin=https://www.magentacloud.de/lnk/6xFRU8hr
downloadmac=https://www.magentacloud.de/lnk/JElx0kia
downloadlinux=https://www.magentacloud.de/lnk/0nFRU6eG
changelog=
 <p><b>Changes from 1.6.0.beta to 1.6.1.beta</b></p>
 <p><i>The scenery database format has changed and the program will ask to erase its own databases if started.</i></p>
 <ul>
   <li>Adapted flight plan calculation, map display and information windows to
       one-way airways and maximum altitude restriction (X-Plane).</li>
   <li>Rhumb line measurement now shows both magnetic and true course where declination is based on origin.</li>
   <li>Improved weather display for nearest station: Added name, distance and map link to reporting station.</li>
   <li>Route string generation is now more robust for malformed and incomplete flight plans.</li>
   <li>Removed &quot;select nothing&quot; click areas in flight plan and procedure search top level labels.
       Added push buttons instead.</li>
   <li>Now erasing wrong airway entries at departure and destination when loading flight plan to avoid problems
       with malformed flight plans from PFPX.</li>
   <li>Fixed error where Documents path was not selected as default if missing simulator.</li>
   <li>Database loading dialog now pops up after erasing incompatible databases.</li>
 </ul>
 <small>
   <p><b>Changes from 1.5.4.develop to 1.6.0.beta</b></p>
   <ul>
     <li>Added display of nearest weather station for X-Plane metar file when showing information of an airport.</li>
     <li>ASP4 weather now supported.</li>
     <li>Changed handling of helipads and fixed display. Now using name as an identifier.</li>
     <li>Aircraft size is now displayed correctly for X-Plane on map and information window.</li>
     <li>Fixed problems with special characters in search (special characters are still treated case sensistive).</li>
     <li>Fixed problem where departure parking was dropped on certain cases like flight plan calculation.</li>
     <li>Fixed crash after copying airspaces.</li>
     <li>Added custom update dialog window that can display a longer message.</li>
     <li>Enabled database file exclusions and add-on override options to X-Plane loader. See options dialog on tab Scenery Library Database.</li>
     <li>Fixed crash when reading X-Plane add-on airports (KLAS).</li>
     <li>X-Plane file codec is now set to UTF-8 to avoid problems with special characters on Windows.</li>
     <li>Added detection of closed airports by name for X-Plane.</li>
     <li>Improved detection of military airports in general and name capitalization for X-Plane.</li>
   </ul>
   <p><b>Changes from 1.4.4 to 1.5.4.develop</b></p>
   <ul>
     <li>
       Full support for X-Plane 11:
       <ul>
         <li>scenery database: Airports, aprons, taxiways, navaids, airways, procedures, </li>
         <li>AI traffic, </li>
         <li>weather, </li>
         <li>copy airspaces from FSX/P3D to X-Plane database,</li>
         <li>FMS file loading/saving and</li>
         <li>moving map (needs included Little XpConnect plugin).</li>
       </ul>
     </li>
     <li>Automatic update check with settings in options dialog on tab startup.</li>
     <li>Speed limit for procedure segments.</li>
     <li>Fixed multiple problems with magnetic declination by using magdec.bgl file.</li>
     <li>Can now load FMS, FLP and FS9 ini-style PLN flight plan formats.</li>
     <li>Several problems fixed when loading FSX/P3D scenery databases and P3D v4 add-on.xml.</li>
     <li>Fixed missing encoding in saved PLN files.</li>
     <li>Shows startup positions now in the information window.</li>
     <li>Added clickspots in top labels to clear selections in procedure search and flight plan.</li>
     <li>Added donation link to help menu and about dialog (not active yet).</li>
   </ul>
 </small>

